Coronavirus guidance is being updated.
Read what you can and cannot do

This page gives you guidance on how to stay safely in the Marshall Islands as a visitor, if you are unable to return to the UK.
Everyone should comply with the measures put in place in the Marshall Islands to limit the spread of coronavirus (COVID-19).
Moving around in the Marshall Islands
Marshall Islands authorities have introduced a number of precautionary measures, including a total suspension of international travellers coming into RMI. Domestic air travel between Majuro and Kwajalein on international airlines is also no longer permitted.
Health
Your emotional and mental wellbeing is important. Read guidance on how to look after your mental wellbeing and mental health
